issue.body: Could u pls let users to control the model downing and folder？the pipeline driving people crazy abt the models management！！！！！！！

comment.body:
Reverse engineering the code, it appears that it expects a repo name like: `black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev`, which it then uses to pull from hugging face, with the final cloning being of this here: https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev/tree/main

The way I think it is intended to work is you first use the other model loader that requires the HF token, and once you've downloaded it into your cache, you can swap out to use the "local loader" to grab what is actually a cached version of the remote repo.

(Assuming I understood that correctly, note to the author: Maybe you could just use a single node that uses the token if and only if it's needed and provided?)
